This command can take a long time to run. You then parse the file you saved the output to with the following command
bgp-subnet-parse.pl <OUTFILE>

fields.title: Enumerate Subnets Advertised via BGP

fields.title: Perform NMAP Scan of All Live Ports
fields.help_base:
-sS 
     TCP SYN scan
-Pn 
     No ping
-v 
     Verbose output
-A 
     Enables OS detection, version detection, script scanning and traceroute
-p <ALL_LIVE_PORTS> 
     All live ports discovered by Masscan (separate with commas)
-oA <OUTFILE> 
     Sets output to all three major formats.
-iL <ALL_CIDR_NETS_AND_IPS>
     Takes new-line separated file as input.

fields.title: Perform Masscan of Common Ports
fields.description:
Sample Email you can send to client:
The first task for the internal testing is to enumerate live network ranges. We do this by scanning all private IP ranges (RFC 1918) for about one dozen common ports. We’ll typically do this after hours (it typically takes a good 8 hours to complete). We have control over the packets per second, we don’t expect any issues, but potential issues include network slowness/latency issues. Thus, if you anyone experiences ANYTHING related to network slowness they can reach out to us immediately. Also remember that if anyone on your team suspects our testing is causing an issue they can disconnect our device from the network – this will not ruin anything we’re doing and we can restart after the problem has been addressed. Let me know if you have any questions or want to schedule a quick call to discuss. Thanks!
fields.help_base:
-oG <OUTFILE> 
     Sets output format to grepable.. (Other format options include binary (-oB), XML (-oX), JSON (-oJ)and simple list (-oL).)
-p21,22,23,53,139,389,445,80,443,1433,1443,3389,8080,8443 
--rate 1000 
-iL <ALL_CIDR_NETS>
     Accepts file input. Can be run on a single CIDR net by removing -iL flag.
--interactive
     shows the results in real time on the console

fields.title: Enumerate Outbound Firewall Rules
fields.description:
egadz.metasploit.com
This commond enumerates the TCP ports which are allowed outbound to the Internet. This currently uses the host egadz.metasploit.com which is configured to reply to all SYN packets, making it appear that all ports on the host are open. Be sure to perform an nslookup of the host to make sure the IP address has not changed.

fields.title: Gather Initial Scope

fields.title: Attach Signed Statement of Work
fields.description: Attach the statement of work to this task as a reference and create a note with the major points, as well as anything unique.

fields.title: Kick Off Call
fields.description:
Introduce Team on both sides

Contact Information
 LeetSys Project Lead & Emergency Contact Info
 Client Project Lead & Emergency Contact Info

Confirm Scope 
 Target IPs, Target Websites
 Anything specifically avoided/blacklisted
 
Testing Windows
 Dates and Times
 
Check before Exploitation & How much Oversight

fields.title: Internal Team Discussion
fields.description:
Cover at least the following

The Client - Name, Address, Overview, Industry and Sector, Size
How we obtained the work
The type of project and any unique elements
Targeted Assets (primary and secondary)

Tentative dates, timelines and deadlines

Define project roles
 project manager  
 technical lead  
 testers

Review project methodology and discuss any recent additions to methodology

Open floor to question, thoughts, comments

fields.title: Peer Review Report
fields.description:
Spelling & Grammar Check
Verify no other client names
Verify no data should be sanitized (eg; passwords, sensitive emails, etc)

fields.title: Deliver Report
fields.description: Deliver the report to client.

fields.title: Perform Masscan of Common Ports
fields.description:
Sample Email you can send to client:
The first task for the internal testing is to enumerate live network ranges. We do this by scanning all private IP ranges (RFC 1918) for about one dozen common ports. We’ll typically do this after hours (it typically takes a good 8 hours to complete). We have control over the packets per second, we don’t expect any issues, but potential issues include network slowness/latency issues. Thus, if you anyone experiences ANYTHING related to network slowness they can reach out to us immediately. Also remember that if anyone on your team suspects our testing is causing an issue they can disconnect our device from the network – this will not ruin anything we’re doing and we can restart after the problem has been addressed. Let me know if you have any questions or want to schedule a quick call to discuss. Thanks!

--rate 1000

--interactive
     shows the results in real time on the console

fields.title: Enumerate Outbound Firewall Rules
fields.description:
egadz.metasploit.com
This commond enumerates the TCP ports which are allowed outbound to the Internet. This currently uses the host egadz.metasploit.com which is configured to reply to all SYN packets, making it appear that all ports on the host are open. Be sure to perform an nslookup of the host to make sure the IP address has not changed.
